The key innovation we could explore lies in *adaptive fusion*: developing architectures that dynamically modulate the integration of global and local features based on contextual demands. For instance, predicting a rare or ambiguous relation (e.g., “acquired” vs. “partnered”) may require more reliance on global context, while common relations might be resolved locally. 

